.TH KALK 1 "2026-03-15" "kalk" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kalk \- a minimal terminal spreadsheet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kalk
.RI [ file.csv ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kalk
is a minimal VisiCalc-inspired spreadsheet for the terminal.
It reads and writes CSV files and supports formulas, cell formatting,
row/column operations, and title locking.
Supports both traditional (@SUM(A1...A4)) and Google Sheets-style
(=SUM(A1:A4)) formula syntax.
.PP
The grid supports columns A\-IV (256) and rows 1\-1024.
.SH NAVIGATION
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Move cursor
.TP
.B Tab
Move to next column
.TP
.B Enter
Move to next row
.TP
.B Home
Jump to cell A1 (or first unlocked cell)
.TP
.B >
Go to a specific cell (type reference, e.g. B12)
.SH ENTERING DATA
.PP
Type a number, formula, or label directly. Formulas start with
.BR + ", " \- ", " ( ", " @ ", or " = .
Labels can be entered directly or prefixed with
.BR \(dq .
.TP
.B Backspace/Delete
Clear current cell
.TP
.B !
Force recalculation
.SH FORMULAS
.PP
Formulas support arithmetic operators (+, \-, *, /), comparison operators
(<, >, <=, >=, =, <>, !=), parentheses, cell references (e.g. A1, $B$2),
and functions:
.TP
.B @SUM(range)
Sum of values in range (e.g. @SUM(A1...A10) or =SUM(A1:A10))
.TP
.B @AVERAGE(range)
Mean of values in range
.TP
.B @MIN(range)
Minimum value in range
.TP
.B @MAX(range)
Maximum value in range
.TP
.B @COUNT(range)
Count of numeric cells in range
.TP
.B @IF(cond, tval, fval)
If cond is non-zero and not NAN, returns tval, else fval
.TP
.B @ABS(expr)
Absolute value
.TP
.B @INT(expr)
Integer part (truncate)
.TP
.B @SQRT(expr)
Square root
.TP
.B @ROUND(expr, places)
Round to N decimal places (default 0)
.TP
.B @ROUNDUP(expr, places)
Round up to N decimal places (default 0)
.TP
.B @ROUNDDOWN(expr, places)
Round down to N decimal places (default 0)
.TP
.B @CEILING(expr)
Round up to nearest integer
.TP
.B @FLOOR(expr)
Round down to nearest integer
.PP
Functions can be used with or without the @ prefix (e.g. SUM(A1:A10)
works the same as @SUM(A1:A10)). IF and ROUND/ROUNDUP/ROUNDDOWN
accept comma-separated arguments (e.g. IF(A1, A2, A3)).
Ranges can use either
.B ...
(e.g. A1...A10) or
.B :
(e.g. A1:A10).
.PP
Cell references can use
.B $
to mark absolute columns or rows:
.B $A1
(absolute column),
.B A$1
(absolute row),
.B $A$1
(both).
Absolute references are preserved during replicate operations.
.SH COMMANDS
.PP
Press
.B /
to enter command mode. Available commands:
.TP
.B /B
Blank current cell (clear value, keep format)
.TP
.B /C
Clear entire spreadsheet
.TP
.B /D R\fR,\fB /D C
Delete current row or column
.TP
.B /I R\fR,\fB /I C
Insert row or column at cursor
.TP
.B /F \fIformat\fR
Set cell format: L(eft) R(ight) I(nteger) G(eneral) D(efault) $(dollar) %(percent) *(bar graph)
.TP
.B /GC
Set global column width (4\-20)
.TP
.B /GF \fIformat\fR
Set global default format
.TP
.B /M
Move row or column (use arrow keys to drag, Enter to confirm, Esc to cancel)
.TP
.B /R
Replicate (copy) cells. Select source range, then target location. Formulas
adjust relative references automatically.
.TP
.B /SL
Load CSV file
.TP
.B /SS
Save CSV file
.TP
.B /SQ
Save and quit
.TP
.B /TV\fR,\fB /TH\fR,\fB /TB\fR,\fB /TN
Lock title rows/columns: Vertical, Horizontal, Both, or None
.TP
.B /Q
Quit (prompts if unsaved changes)
.SH FILES
.PP
kalk reads and writes standard CSV files. Formulas are stored as entered
(e.g. +A1+B1) and recalculated on load.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit
.TP
.B 1
Error (e.g. failed to load file)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B kalk
Start with an empty spreadsheet
.TP
.B kalk budget.csv
Open an existing CSV file
